results.title: Q1
results.sql: SELECT DayOfWeek, count(*) AS c FROM ontime WHERE Year >= 2000 AND Year <= 2008 GROUP BY DayOfWeek ORDER BY c DESC;

results.title: Q2
results.sql: SELECT DayOfWeek, count(*) AS c FROM ontime WHERE DepDelay>10 AND Year >= 2000 AND Year <= 2008 GROUP BY DayOfWeek ORDER BY c DESC;

results.title: Q3
results.sql: SELECT Origin, count(*) AS c FROM ontime WHERE DepDelay>10 AND Year >= 2000 AND Year <= 2008 GROUP BY Origin ORDER BY c DESC LIMIT 10;

results.title: Q4
results.sql: SELECT IATA_CODE_Reporting_Airline AS Carrier, count() FROM ontime WHERE DepDelay>10 AND Year = 2007 GROUP BY Carrier ORDER BY count() DESC;

results.title: Q5
results.sql: SELECT IATA_CODE_Reporting_Airline AS Carrier, avg(cast(DepDelay>10 as Int8))*1000 AS c3 FROM ontime WHERE Year=2007 GROUP BY Carrier ORDER BY c3 DESC;

results.title: Q6
results.sql: SELECT IATA_CODE_Reporting_Airline AS Carrier, avg(cast(DepDelay>10 as Int8))*1000 AS c3 FROM ontime WHERE Year>=2000 AND Year <=2008 GROUP BY Carrier ORDER BY c3 DESC;

results.title: Q7
results.sql: SELECT IATA_CODE_Reporting_Airline AS Carrier, avg(DepDelay) * 1000 AS c3 FROM ontime WHERE Year >= 2000 AND Year <= 2008 GROUP BY Carrier;

results.title: Q8
results.sql: SELECT Year, avg(DepDelay) FROM ontime GROUP BY Year;

results.title: Q9
results.sql: SELECT Year, count(*) as c1 FROM ontime GROUP BY Year;

results.title: Q10
results.sql: SELECT avg(cnt) FROM (SELECT Year,Month,count(*) AS cnt FROM ontime WHERE DepDel15=1 GROUP BY Year,Month) a;

results.title: Q11
results.sql: SELECT avg(c1) FROM (SELECT Year,Month,count(*) AS c1 FROM ontime GROUP BY Year,Month) a;

results.title: Q12
results.sql: SELECT OriginCityName, DestCityName, count(*) AS c FROM ontime GROUP BY OriginCityName, DestCityName ORDER BY c DESC LIMIT 10;

results.title: Q13
results.sql: SELECT OriginCityName, count(*) AS c FROM ontime GROUP BY OriginCityName ORDER BY c DESC LIMIT 10;
